a static class$ call just initializes Object. But the public API would fail without the closure constructor, leading to ClassCast or NoSuch errors. Maybe we can remove the public API test since the focus is on dynamic calls and it’s not necessary. If it fails due to a missing constructor, that could complicate closures being passed correctly. So, removing that test makes sense, allowing use of class$ as a simple Object instead.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering library code and class loading**\\n\\nI’m thinking that the library code might run into class loading issues due to other tests. There’s no public path test, but a class with the same name that doesn't extend Closure could cause problems if the response.path lacks a content type call. That would only affect our test, though. It seems the \\\"active closure\\\" API call may not be necessary, so I should consider simplifying things by removing it to reduce potential conflicts.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_6bE95TmHyDHvQg1E2qrwqNua|fc_092b152a47ada7d6016a01af790a3c819eac454223059e3beb", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "grep -R \"\\.path(\\|path(\" -n tests/src/io.rest-assured/rest-assured/5.5.0/src/test/java/io_rest_assured/rest_assured | grep -E \"Response|RestAssuredResponseOptions\" | head -20"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 3638, "output": 911, "cacheRead": 72192, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 76741, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778495335418, "responseId": "resp_092b152a47ada7d6016a01af6830ec819eb8c18cd765f9b578"}}
