r, leading to ClassCast or NoSuch errors. Maybe we can remove the public API test since the focus is on dynamic calls and it’s not necessary. If it fails due to a missing constructor, that could complicate closures being passed correctly. So, removing that test makes sense, allowing use of class$ as a simple Object instead.\n\n**Considering library code and class loading**\n\nI’m thinking that the library code might run into class loading issues due to other tests. There’s no public path test, but a class with the same name that doesn't extend Closure could cause problems if the response.path lacks a content type call. That would only affect our test, though. It seems the \"active closure\" API call may not be necessary, so I should consider simplifying things by removing it to reduce potential conflicts.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_092b152a47ada7d6016a01af697b20819e97f41a90986632bf\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqAa95vsNxOcXgp_D9f6Z-UCom23j6-Jzip3k5WBzTuK6YdCGvzTsqQJe2sd2CAyLrBnFwkr5KKii9DwfU8uK_AY-5jHDU7TNfvml0njto1VPxuSVYIW--UwLpVOU5aY-i9VcusDw0cesk82CFGjnTFWeD4yftrcjm0xNTO0pTA_R7g73WVCfp7-C1vNLuQOgTd1jVsT2TvKWDevI9vZBkLTHo19Qlf_eCNRIqL3wc1Rx1N_JmCZNj05OreiS5ink8Ww2G9gmNOpMobu213lpeu7FBEy3K-5hMx2xl02m68O_6eUAikRVYvIlK_CT6oIunaZA_1iSmKukBVeFo0OJeyZBLXGxeJ0JuBB7T5W0dGcMucq8BXgCuY-CqmopfUWiY7dRN7nQD-KtXx0r2EmbzER2IYUNvbaDL8jGAfosl4k3AxTWFBhI9sQtUEjKgqv7nOP2qixqoDkPWfly1Zij7JyREz4a4_GUVEBlLPPQtXc4Pxb1-zYWprk8MN2dGcp9r0FtW4rvsL2ILiV80m6rai38YxerJ_bBo33DoNJEbvt930zBASUf9cHMQuJxc8T5xotD66VREhavuksWXCTD4L8BEV9WyYvs7YsekF87XfKFqATQencHUmRMS9uGZvHW66yMosVo2e53YTIrkk4Tngj4vBCD_rCuD43WeGg71i4lSMO6xQcPEwLOo8pLzvsuOVYSO-jCIglZrfcMarq5dV97_bkJs2IhofFTtuB4_6-0ad6uO7UWyBN8jnWarPxrObttQUIAk2oyZpafspM7ou6j37vXIqH15xnG89NxPkLWZcTKuER4jy3Zq7014OvnJaKK2Nh4b3xvNN5qBFtNl7dYeebI-FQnU9uMOQIugmP-LoEPh3T7uwTwVZpIDZ5_cqrg5uywO73Mva0HBnxSAqIWJxyIiVuoedal9YAK20ebdZmvEjVOaYrBZzPXef9o4DXoFpQpcMXgPLh1P7zuHl8UoemHyq8PHBcAbDwjCg3Pmo1bCdlZFd180139k5yyNP4BLtvFZWocv2L